Strategic Thinking. Execution Excellence. Real-World Change.

We’re a dynamic and growing accounting and advisory firm seeking a Senior Manager – IT Data & Digital Transformation to lead and deliver critical, business-wide change. This isn’t a role for someone who just speaks the language of transformation — it’s for someone who’s lived it, led it, and delivered it.

Based in our North Sydney office with regular travel to other offices, you’ll be a connector of people, systems, and strategy. You’ll build strong relationships with our Partners, drive execution from the ground up, role model excellence and excution and bring our digital, data, and technology capabilities to the next level.

Your Role
Own and drive digital transformation initiatives, aligning our tech and data platforms with business growth and client expectations.
Lead the selection, implementation, and optimisation of what is the best practice roadmap incorporating our systems including APS, MYOB, and integrated cloud-based platforms.
Deliver a scalable data management and consolidation strategy, with a strong preference for platforms like Snowflake to unify reporting, analytics, and decision-making.
Champion cloud and infrastructure transformation, particularly within Microsoft Azure environments.
Oversee cybersecurity strategy and compliance, ensuring our digital operations remain secure, resilient, and scalable.
Lead change management programs with empathy, helping teams adopt and embed new technologies and ways of working.
Build and lead project teams to deliver outcomes on time, on budget, and in alignment with the firm's strategic goals.
Be a trusted partner to senior leaders – turning business needs into clear, executable plans and measurable results.
What You’ll Bring
Proven experience delivering complex digital, IT, and data transformation within professional services, finance, or similar sectors.
Deep familiarity with core platforms such as APS, MYOB, Snowflake, Azure, and modern BI/analytics environments (e.g., Power BI).
A track record of hands-on delivery – from concept to go-live – with responsibility for both project outcomes and adoption.
Strong grounding in cybersecurity principles, risk management, and data governance.
Demonstrated success leading change management across multi-site, people-first businesses.
Outstanding communication and stakeholder engagement skills – you build credibility and trust across all levels.
Relevant tertiary qualifications (e.g., Information Systems, Business Technology, Computer Science), and certifications in project/change management (Agile, PMP, PROSCI, etc.) and evidence of continuous professional development is preferred and highly regarded.
Who You Are
Hungry to make a difference and build something lasting
Humble enough to listen, learn, and lead with empathy
Accountable and hands-on – not just strategic, but delivery-focused
A natural relationship builder, confident travelling to offices, spending time with teams, and leading change from the ground
A technologist with business acumen – you understand the impact of systems on people, performance, and growth. You know the tech stack but you know budgets and the value of impact of what you're proposing from a $ perspective.
What’s In It For You
A senior leadership role in a growing, future-focused firm that values people and progress
Opportunity to shape and execute a firm-wide transformation agenda
Work closely with partners, directors, and senior stakeholders to deliver visible outcomes
Competitive salary + performance incentives + professional development
A supportive, collaborative, and agile work culture with flexibility and travel
Apply Now

If you’re ready to bring strategic clarity, operational execution, and real-world change to a firm on the rise – we’d love to hear from you.

Apply with your CV and a short note outlining your transformation experience – especially where you've helped teams adopt and thrive with platforms like Snowflake, Azure, and others.

Bluefin Resources is seeking a Senior Business Analyst to work on an enterprise-wide implementation of a new Project Portfolio Management (PPM) tool (Planview) for a Big Four Bank.
 
This is a business-facing role not a technical position. The Senior Business Analyst will work closely with internal stakeholders and the external vendor to ensure a smooth end-to-end implementation, aligning business requirements with delivery outcomes.
 
Key Responsibilities:
• Lead and support business analysis activities across the full implementation lifecycle of the new PPM tool.
• Engage with senior business stakeholders to capture, validate and document business requirements.
• Liaise between the business and vendor teams to ensure alignment and clarity of deliverables.
• Develop and maintain process documentation, user guides and implementation materials.
 
Experience Required:
• Proven end-to-end experience in large-scale system implementations, ideally enterprise-wide.
• Previous experience in financial services is essential.
• Exposure to PPM tools such as Planview or Clarity will be highly regarded.
• Strong communication and stakeholder management skills, with experience engaging across all levels of an organisation.
• Ability to operate in a fast-paced, enterprise environment with multiple stakeholders.
 
This is a daily rate contract role based in Sydney CBD, paying $950 per day + super. The role requires three days per week in the office. Please apply using the link below and attach your resume in Word format.

Drive actionable insights & reports from sales, marketing & audience data.
Hybrid working, sociable team and career development opportunities.


Company Overview


CoStar Group (NASDAQ: CSGP) is a leading global provider of commercial and residential real estate information, analytics, and online marketplaces. Included in the S&P 500 Index and the NASDAQ 100, CoStar Group is on a mission to digitize the world's real estate, empowering all people to discover properties, insights and connections that improve their businesses and lives.


We have been living and breathing the world of real estate information and online marketplaces for over 35 years, giving us the perspective to create truly unique and valuable offerings to our customers. We've continually refined, transformed, and perfected our approach to our business, creating a language that has become standard in our industry, for our customers, and even our competitors. We continue that effort today and are always working to improve and drive innovation. This is how we deliver for our customers, our employees, and investors. By equipping the brightest minds with the best resources available, we provide an invaluable edge in real estate.


About Domain:

Domain is a leading property technology and services marketplace that is home to one of the largest portfolios of property brands in Australia, including the Domain, Allhomes and Commercial Real Estate (CRE) platforms. In 2025, Domain became part of CoStar Group (NASDAQ: CSGP), a global leader in commercial real estate information, analytics, online marketplaces and 3D digital twin technology. Together, Domain and CoStar Group is dedicated to digitising the world's real estate, empowering all people to discover properties, insights, and connections that improve their businesses and lives.


About the Role

As a Commercial Insights Analyst and under the wing of an experienced Commercial Performance Manager, you will drive data into actionable insights for internal teams across our AllHomes and Agent Solutions products. Whether it's deciphering large data sets, or providing powerful visualisation and reporting across sales marketing and audience insights, you will be an integral part of helping sales teams to sell more and sell faster.


Sitting within a team that is only just scratching the surface with the data they have available, this is a unique opportunity to engage in interesting and impactful work that is in huge demand across the business, enjoying a great deal of autonomy and ownership of your work, and where team growth is certainly on the horizon.


Why Join Us:

We're the right size business for you to make a real impact, with a workplace culture where you can be you. Perks of the role include:



Our much-loved approach to flexible hybrid working;
Mentoring and leadership programs, with access to Learning & Development tools;
First rate parental leave and support for working parents;
Regular social events including our famous Innovation Days



In a typical day you can expect to:

Partner with Leaders of business segments to provide strategic and tactical input and recommendations based on data and insights.
Participate in Quarterly Sales Reviews and associated analysis & story telling.
Use a range of data sources to uncover actionable insights and prioritise accordingly.
Manage the insights and reports pipeline requests and their respective stakeholders' expectations.
Develop reports in Tableau that are scalable throughout our sales teams.
Develop and maintain new dashboards and reports for sales revenue, target setting and tracking, and platforms for strategic storytelling.
Get actively involved in ad-hoc projects at the request of Sales Leadership.


Our Ideal Person:

Bachelor's Degree required from an accredited, not-for-profit university or college.
Experience analysing and interpreting sales data into actionable insights.
High level Tableau experience (e.g. complex dashboards and reports).
Experience querying data using SQL.
Experience driving end-to-end insights led programs.
A level of confidence to have tricky conversations when needed.
Comfortable to present complex data to non-data people.
Able to work autonomously.



What's Next?

We'll give your application the thoughtful attention it deserves and get back to you as soon as possible. If there's a match, one of our recruitment consultants will reach out-so keep your phone handy! We're genuinely excited about the chance to work together and make a meaningful impact.
